sentences: Boris Dlugosch (German pronunciation: [boːʁɪs deːlʊˈɡɔʃ]; born August 2, 1968) is a German house music producer from Hamburg.

Dlugosch had a few occasional hits in the club circuit in the 1990s, beginning with the two tracks created with Mousse T. under the Booom! moniker, "Hold Your Head Up High" and "Keep Pushin'", with vocals by Inaya Day, and "Check It Out (Everybody)", under the alias BMR (a regular partnership with Michi Lange).
It peaked at #16 in the UK Singles Chart in June 2001.
In 2013 Dlugosch played on the song "Step Together" by Joe Goddard of his EP, "Taking Over"
Dlugosch's name achieved some fame in the year 1999 thanks to his remix of Moloko's "Sing It Back", which became a club music phenomenon.
As a producer, however, Dlugosch's first works, in the early 1990s, were in the happy hardcore genre, working alongside Gary D.
Boris Dlugosch started his career as a DJ in the German night club Front in the Hammerbrook district of Hamburg.
